 up in diversity. He&apos;s happy and sometimes when I pick him up he doesn&apos;t run to me straight but shows me some friend, or stuff/toys around the classroom, which tells me that he&apos;s comfortable and likes it there."},{"author":"Annie C.","datePublished":"2018-02-13","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"Little Explorers is amazing. It&apos;s located in a. church building but not affiliated with the church (no longer in a home.) We actually switched here from a chain daycare and it was such a refreshing difference. The staff are so caring and personable. They do fun activities and don&apos;t have unreasonable rules like the chain place did. My toddler instantly felt at home and even wanted to stay and read a book with the owner when she first met her. Highly recommend!"},{"author":"Yasmin P.","datePublished":"2016-08-13","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":2},"description":"We went to visit, and the owner didnt even meet us. Apparently she went running and couldnt be bothered, even though we set the appointment with her directly. Her mother was very nice and i could tell the teachers were kind and caring. However, they couldnt find the folder of information we were supposed to receive and leave with. The home was small and cluttered, and probably best suited for older children, and not infants. Very disappointed, not a good first impression at all."},{"author":"Alyssa A.","datePublished":"2019-01-05","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"There are not enough words to describe how much I love Little Explorers and how happy I am to have found such an amazing preschool for my children. The teachers there are so kind and caring to every single child. Both of my daughters have attended the school since September of 2017 and have had such a wonderful experience. They helped to prepare and make sure that my older daughter was beyond ready for kindergarten, which she began in Sept of 2018 and she was ahead of many of her peers in many different aspec